('Finance', 'mid', 'The Expense Dilemma', 'You find a team is consistently over budget but their results are excellent. Do you flag it or let it slide?', '[{"id":"A","label":"Flag it—budget discipline matters regardless of results","why_it_matters":"Shows financial discipline","signals":["budget adherence","process compliance"]},{"id":"B","label":"Understand the why first—maybe their budget needs adjustment","why_it_matters":"Shows investigative approach","signals":["root cause thinking","fairness orientation"]},{"id":"C","label":"Have a private conversation before escalating—give them a chance to correct","why_it_matters":"Shows diplomatic enforcement","signals":["relationship preservation","coaching approach"]}]', '["execution_style", "communication_style"]', 'Each approach balances compliance with context.'),
('Finance', 'senior', 'The Forecast Miss', 'Halfway through the quarter, it is clear revenue will miss forecast by 15%. What do you do?', '[{"id":"A","label":"Immediately communicate to leadership with revised forecast and analysis","why_it_matters":"Shows transparency","signals":["early warning","honest communication"]},{"id":"B","label":"Work with sales to identify upside opportunities before raising alarm","why_it_matters":"Shows solution orientation","signals":["collaborative problem-solving","optimism"]},{"id":"C","label":"Prepare scenario plans (best case, worst case) before the conversation","why_it_matters":"Shows prepared communication","signals":["contingency planning","thorough analysis"]}]', '["communication_style", "problem_solving_vectors"]', 'All responses demonstrate financial leadership.'),
('Finance', 'lead', 'The Audit Finding', 'External auditors found a control weakness that has existed for years. It is not material but needs fixing. Leadership is resistant to the cost. What do you do?', '[{"id":"A","label":"Advocate strongly—compliance risk is not worth the savings","why_it_matters":"Shows compliance commitment","signals":["risk awareness","advocacy"]},{"id":"B","label":"Present options—minimum fix vs comprehensive fix with cost comparison","why_it_matters":"Shows pragmatic problem-solving","signals":["option framing","cost-benefit thinking"]},{"id":"C","label":"Get auditor guidance on timeline to buy time for budget planning","why_it_matters":"Shows strategic navigation","signals":["stakeholder management","timeline negotiation"]}]', '["cognitive_patterns", "communication_style"]', 'Each approach shows professional judgment.'),

